### mergeFromObjectFile() {#ad41848e26234890d2d908a09f6709022}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::CodeGenDataReader::mergeFromObjectFile (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/objectfile">object::ObjectFile</a> &#42; Obj, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/outlinedhashtreerecord">OutlinedHashTreeRecord</a> &amp; GlobalOutlineRecord, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/stablefunctionmaprecord">StableFunctionMapRecord</a> &amp; GlobalFunctionMapRecord, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a3f07bd5ee30b6a57ddc214f64d5fd941">stable&#95;hash</a> &#42; CombinedHash=nullptr)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Extract the cgdata embedded in sections from the given object file and merge them into the GlobalOutlineRecord.

This is a static helper that is used by <code>llvm-cgdata --merge</code> or ThinLTO&#39;s two-codegen rounds. Optionally, <code>CombinedHash</code> can be used to compuate the combined hash of the merged data.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/cgdata/codegendatareader-h/#l00066">66</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/cgdata/codegendatareader-h">CodeGenDataReader.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/cgdata/codegendatareader-cpp/#l00033">33</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/cgdata/codegendatareader-cpp">CodeGenDataReader.cpp</a>.
